The White House Press Secretary issued a statement expressing condolences on the passing of Sheikh Mohammed Sayyed Tantawi, a prominent Egyptian cleric and the grand sheikh of Al-Azhar University. The statement highlights Sheikh Tantawi's role as a voice for faith and tolerance, respected in Muslim communities globally. It also mentions his hospitality during President Obama's visit to Cairo in June. The statement concludes by offering thoughts and prayers to Sheikh Tantawi's family and those mourning his loss.